# 📊 Customer Churn Prediction

This project predicts whether a customer will churn (leave the service) based on their account and service usage data using Machine Learning.

---

## 🚀 Project Overview

Customer churn is a major problem for subscription-based businesses.  
This model uses a **Random Forest Classifier** to analyze customer data and predict churn.

---

## 📂 Dataset

- Source: Telco Customer Churn Dataset
- File: `dataset/churn.csv`
- Target column: `Churn` (Yes / No)

---

## 🧠 Technologies Used

- Python 🐍
- Pandas
- Scikit-learn
- Random Forest Classifier

---

## ⚙️ Workflow

1. Load dataset
2. Drop unnecessary columns (`customerID`)
3. Convert `TotalCharges` to numeric
4. Handle missing values
5. Encode categorical features
6. Split data into train/test sets
7. Train Random Forest model
8. Evaluate performance

---

## 🧪 Model Used

- RandomForestClassifier (Scikit-learn)

---

## 📊 Results

- Accuracy: ~78–80%
- Good performance on non-churn class
- Moderate performance on churn class (needs improvement due to class imbalance)

---

